###      Announcement
 Clients are assigned one Tuesday/month, 1st, 2nd, 3rd or 4th for pickup.  Clients must bring their blue Pantry card to the Pantry to receive food.  New clients who are not registered will receive food, but need to bring proof of residency and complete an application on arrival.


### Who Are We?
####  The Branch Area Food Pantry, **an all volunteer organization,**  serves approximately 115 families every Tuesday, about 475 families each month. We rely on and value the support of our generous community
2021 presented a huge challenge to the Pantry. Between generous community members, financial donations,  In-kind donations of literally tons of food distributed by an amazing group of volunteers, we met the needs of the community and have been able to revise our procedures to meet the challenges of 2022.
THANK YOU!  The Pantry is truly blessed.







### A SHOUT OUT GOES TO---
### ***We truly appreciate the generosity and support of our community!***
![The Stamp Out Hunger® Food Drive](https://about.usps.com/newsroom/local-releases/fl/2022/images/stamp-out-hunger.jpg)
**THANK YOU  Coldwater mail carriers, to our terrific supporters who donated foods and to Wal-Mart Distribution volunteers.  On Saturday, May 7, mail carriers picked up over 3700 pounds of canned and dry foods from around Branch Co and delivered them to the Pantry.   Thanks to our Wal-Mart volunteers for sorting and organizing this massive collection of food allowing us to distribute it in the weeks to come. Way to go!!!!**
##### Regardless of the size of the donation, we appreciate the generosity of all, as we share the foods with our clients.


 
  
### We are grateful to so many donors....
##### The kindness of the community keeps the Pantry alive.  With dozens of local businesses, churches, financial institutions and hundreds of generous citizens,  there is no way to provide individual acknowledgement for each donation.  Know that we appreciate your contribution and promise to use it to continue with our mission of providing food and hope to our community.


  







